    - get_available_choices(): return list of choices valid under current GameState
    - choose(choice): apply effects and move to target node
    - is_end(): whether current node has no available choices
    - to_dict()/from_dict(data): serialize/restore full game session, including state and position

- GameState
  - Purpose: Track dynamic variables that shape the storyline (items, relationships, variables, flags, visited nodes).
  - Key methods:
    - add_item(item), remove_item(item), has_item(item)
    - adjust_var(name, delta), set_var(name, value), get_var(name, default)
    - adjust_relationship(name, delta), get_relationship(name)
    - set_flag(name, value), is_flag(name)
    - to_dict()/from_dict(data): serialize/restore state

- StoryNode
  - Purpose: Single narrative segment with text and branching choices.
  - Fields: node_id, text, choices (list of Choice)
  - Method: available_choices(state): choices whose conditions pass under state

- Choice
  - Purpose: One possible player decision at a node.
  - Fields: text, target, conditions, effects
  - Methods: is_available(state), apply_effects(state)

- Condition checking helpers
  - Purpose: Evaluate structured conditions attached to a choice against GameState.
  - Supported condition keys: items_have, items_not_have, vars_min, vars_max, vars_eq, relationships_min, flags_set, flags_not_set, visited_nodes_include, visited_nodes_exclude

- Storage helpers
  - Purpose: Save/load the session to/from JSON files.

- GUI (Tkinter)
  - StoryApp (Tk root)
    - StartFrame: New Game, Load Game
    - GameFrame: Narrative display, dynamic choice buttons, sidebars for Items, Relationships, Variables, controls for Save/Load/Restart

- Story data (story_data.py)
  - Purpose: Structured dictionary of nodes, choices, and conditions/effects powering the story.

